Question

What does it mean to SAVE the situation?

 
 
 
 

Answer: c) stop, appreciate, validate, explore

 

Rationale:

When a difficult situation has occurred with a patient, Schachter and colleagues (2009) suggest that you stop what you are doing. Next, appreciate what is going on with your patient. This involves taking time to understand what is happening and to help the patient with the situation. Validate the patients experience and then explore how to take the next step.
